Google recently announced end-to-end encryption for Gmail, but there's a catch—it's only for business users, and their organizations manage the encryption keys. That means admins can access emails at any time. Linus and Luke discuss the reality of privacy in corporate communication tools like Gmail, Slack, and Teams, and why it's important to understand who can really see your messages.

Intel and TSMC have reportedly struck a preliminary deal to form a joint chipmaking venture, with TSMC taking a 20% stake in Intel's U.S. fabs. With Intel posting its first loss since 1986 and the U.S. pushing to bolster domestic chip production, this move could reshape the future of semiconductors. But is this just further consolidating TSMC's dominance? Linus and Luke weigh in on what this might mean for the industry and who, if anyone, can challenge TSMC's grip on high-performance chips.
